==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Goshawk
<hw>Gos"hawk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>g⟦omac⟧shafuc</ets>, lit., goosehawk; or Icel.
<ets>g⟦amac⟧shaukr</ets>. See <er>Goose</er>, and <er>Hawk</er> the
bird.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any large hawk of the genus
<gen>Astur</gen>, of which many species and varieties are known. The
European (<spn>Astur palumbarius</spn>) and the American (<spn>A.
atricapillus</spn>) are the best known species. They are noted for their
powerful flight, activity, and courage. The Australian goshawk (<spn>A.
Nov⟦ae⟧-Hollandi⟦ae⟧</spn>) is pure white.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

